<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id9069fcbf-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6" identifier="/us/usc/t22/s4082"><num value="4082">§ 4082.</num><heading> Loan of household effects</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Secretary may, as a means of eliminating transportation costs, provide members of the Service with basic household furnishing and equipment for use on a loan basis in personally owned or leased residences.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id9069fcc0-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6">(<ref href="/us/pl/96/465/tI/s902">Pub. L. 96–465, title I, § 902</ref>, <date date="1980-10-17">Oct. 17, 1980</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/94/2127">94 Stat. 2127</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
